+# Human Review Policy
+
+Model output is decision support. A human reviewer remains responsible for care-management action decisions.
+
+Manual review is required when inputs are invalid, extreme but technically valid, partial-year enrollment materially affects interpretation, the profile is out of expected training bounds, or the recommendation would materially affect a beneficiary.
+
+Reviewers may override recommendations. Override volume and rationale should be monitored as operational feedback and possible drift evidence.
